5. Conclusion

With the many conceptions of logic and the many different
philosophical projects under the heading of ontology, there are many
problems that are in the intersection of these areas. We have touched
on several above, but there are also others. Although there is no
single problem about the relationship between logic and ontology,
there are many interesting connections between them, some closely
connected to central philosophical questions. The references and links
below are intended to provide a more in depth discussions of these
topics.
